OL,3,CEx-pro Stewart: 'I can't tie my
OL,4,Cshoelaces any more'
OL,6,FFormer professional footballer Marcus
OL,7,FStewart has spoken about his battle
OL,8,Fwith motor neurone disease () as he
OL,9,Fprepares for a 175-mile fundraising
OL,10,Fwalk.
OL,12,FThe ex-Huddersfield Town player says
OL,13,Fhe is "lucky" to have so far escaped
OL,14,Fthe worst effects of the life-limiting
OL,15,Fcondition since his diagnosis in
OL,16,FSeptember 2022.
OL,18,FBut the 51-year-old says he has become
OL,19,Fmuch "slower".
